JAPAN
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting
the beautiful, the monumental and the picturesque. His watercolors grace more than forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad.
JAPAN is a land of contrasts It can display the most neon-lit, skyscrapered and expressway-lined
face, yet finds its inspiration in the quiet beauty of the graceful Tori Gate and Mt. Fuji, pictred here.
The Japanese can run their trains at lightening speed, yet spend hours on a small conversational
courtesy Here you will find graceful perfection and formality contrasted with vigorous commerce.
Among the many stylish hotels in the capital city of Tokyo is the Keio Plaza Inter-Continental
Pan Am serves Tokyo on its Round-The-World flights and nonstop daily from New York, San Francisco.
Los Angeles, Honolulu, and Hong Kong. Osaka is served nonstop from Honolulu
